result.execSummary:
The defendant Cyle Ann Kraft was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
In the Wisconsin State Prison System
Consecutive to: any other sentence
Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
Court ordered defendant to complete a driver assessment and safety plan.
Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample.

Court ordered defendant to pay a $600 fine, plus DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements.  Defendant given three years to pay; to be paid while on probation.  Should defendant get revoked, monies are ordered taken from prison funds not to exceed 25%.

miscConds.notes: PROBATION CONDITIONS (and extended supervision, if revoked):

No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician for her mental or physical needs and only as long as deemed medically necessary. No alcohol; urine screens.
Seek and maintain employment. Job and vocational training.

Pay balance remaining of the ($600) fine, costs, surcharges and disbursements.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms. Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.
